description: a(n) = Sum_{ d divides n } q(d), where q(d) = A000009 = number of partitions of d into distinct parts.
comments: Number of partitions of n such that every part occurs with the same multiplicity. - _Vladeta Jovovic_, Oct 22 2004Equals inverse Mobius transform (A051731) * A000009, where the latter begins (1, 1, 2, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 8,...) -  _Gary W. Adamson_, Jun 08 2009
